summary:
Cerebral edema is commonly associated with active stages of neurocysticercosis due to inflammation and cyst presence. Only in the nodular calcified stage, representing healed, stabilized tissue, is edema typically absent because inflammation has ceased.  

Answer Choice: \boxed{D}

The summary focuses solely on clinically relevant facts regarding edema occurrence by stage—specifically identifying its prominence during inflamed/active phases and disappearance upon resolution into calcified form—which directly answers whether an individual stage exhibits no edema without introducing extraneous details.

